      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BELLA VIOLETTA (7) was no match for the winner at Albany last time out when beaten 4.2L as the race favourite. Needs some luck from the wide barrier, but Yuill hops on board and her best form rates highly. Can make her presence felt. TAK GOES BOOM (6) was too good at York earlier this week when running over the top from midfield, scoring by 0.6L. Webster rides now claiming 3kg which means he only rises 0.5kg. Drawn well again and won't be far away. QUEEN NARDI (5) comes through that race behind TAK GOES BOOM where she sat on the speed throughout. This looks to shape similarly and that form looks strong for this race. STAR TESTYMONY (1) hasn't raced since finishing ninth at Pakenham over 2500m two months ago. Kept ticking over with a recent trial at Lark Hill. Among the chances and expected to feature. TOBIAN (8) was beaten 7 lengths into sixth over 1900m at Albany last time out. Well placed and can figure in the finish this time.",
